3 TEXT Elizabeth Goodale&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;Gender: Female&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;Birth: Circa 1638 - Salem, Essex, Massachusetts Bay, British Colonial America&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;Marriage: Circa 1657&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;
4 CONC Marriage: Mar 1674 - Salem, Essex, Massachusetts Bay Colony, British Colonial America&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;Death: From 1692 - Salem, Essex, Massachusetts Bay, British Colonial America&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;Par
4 CONC ents: &lt;a&gt;Robert Goodale&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Kathern Goodale&lt;/a&gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;Spouses: &lt;a&gt;John Smith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;William Bennett&lt;/a&gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;Children: &lt;a
4 CONC &gt;Mary Haskell (born Smith)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;John Smith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Sarah Clark (born Smith)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Elizabeth Smith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Abraham Smith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Grac
4 CONC e Bennett&lt;/a&gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;Siblings: &lt;a&gt;Mary Pease (born Goodale)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Abraham Goodale&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Isaac Goodale&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Sarah Batcheller (born Gooda
4 CONC le)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Zachariah Goodale&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Jacob Goodale&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a&gt;Hannah Kilham (born Goodale)&lt;/a&gt;&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Additional information: &lt;
4 CONC br&gt; &lt;br&gt;LifeSketch: Elizabeth is likely the first child born to her parents in Massachusetts Bay.  She has no birth record, and no marriage record with John Smith.  However, she is mentioned 
4 CONC in her father&#039;s will which was written in 1682.  At that time she was referred to as Elizabeth Bennett.  Her son from her first marriage, John Smith, was also mentioned.  For the full transcript 
4 CONC of this section of the will, see The ancestry of Lydia Harmon, 1755-1836, wife of Joseph Waterhouse ... (attached under Sources).  

There are two children for John and Elizabeth lived in Salem vital 
4 CONC records: 
Smith, Sara, d. John, farrier, and Elizabeth, Oct. 20, 1660. CTR

Smith, Elizabeth, d. John, farrier, and Elizabeth, June 5, 1662. CTR
A farrier is a craftsman who trims and shoes horses&#03
4 CONC 9; hooves.  I think there was more than one John Smith iiving in the area, and John&#039;s occupation was listed as a clarification.  

There is no birth record for her son John Smith, Mary Smith, or 
4 CONC Abraham Smith, but these children are listed in the Lydia Harmon book above.  See page 35.  

This source lists the following chidlren for Elizabeth and her first husband John: 
1.  John Smith - He ma
4 CONC rried Ann Skery February 6, 1689.  HE was a maltster in Salem in 1692.
2. Mary Smith - She married Mark Haskell of Beverly, carpenter, March 20, 1677/8.
3. Sarah Smith - b. Oct. 20, 1660; married John
4 CONC  Clark of Beverly, weaver.
4. Elizabeth Smith - b. June 5, 1662; m. Humphrey Horrill of Beverly, Jan. 10, 1687/8.
5. Abraham Smith - By deed and release from his brother and sisters he acquired the Go
4 CONC odale homestead, which had been left by his grandfather to his mohter, and also the property deeded to her in 1678.  HE conveyed the estate to his son, Nathan, in 1740. 

After her first husband&#039;
4 CONC s death, Elizabeth married, as her second husband, William Bennett.  Her marriage record can be found in Salem vital records: 
Bennett, William, and, wid. Elizabeth Smith, Mar. ––, 1674-5.

Accord
4 CONC ing to Robert Charles Anderson in his Great Migration series (see attached under Sources): &quot;this marriage record as published from the court copy gives the groom&#039;s name as &quot;William,&quo
4 CONC t; but in deeds he is called &quot;Henry,&quot; and these seem to be the more reliable records.&quot;  

I could understand if just the marriage record appeared to call Elizabeth&#039;s husband by the
4 CONC  wrong first name, but that isn&#039;t the case.  William and Elizabeth are also mentioned in the birth record of their daughter Grace: 

Bennett, Grace, d. William and Elizabeth, Feb. ––, 1676. C
4 CONC TR

and William and Elizabeth are also mentioned in the death record for Grace: 

Bennett, Grace, d. William and Elizabeth, abt. Feb. ––, 1676. CTR

Elizabeth&#039;s husband is clearly named Willi
4 CONC am in all these records.
