Died: 25 May 1741, Gloucester, Essex, Massachusetts, United States at age 93&quot;Benjamin Haskell of Gloucester was born in Beverly in 1648 and died in Gl
4 CONC oucester in his ninety-second year. Like his brother he was often a selectman and a deacon of the First Church; also he was a representative to the General Court in 1707. By trade he was a housewright
4 CONC . He married first Mary Riggs by whom he had nine children. After her death in 1697 he married Emma Bond.&quot;

Ref: &quot;Chronicles of the Haskell Family&quot; by Ira J. Haskell, published by Ellis
4 CONC  Printing Co., Lynn, MA, 1943.

Benjamin and his second wife, Emma (Graves) Bond had no issue.

